Kale Salad with Pecorino and Walnuts

1/2 c toasted walnut halves or pieces
1/4 c golden raisins
1 tbsp white wine vinegar
1 tbsp water
1/4 c panko or slightly coarse homemade breadcrumbs
1 tine clove garlic, minced or pressed
coarse or kosher salt
3 tbsp olive oil
1 bunch (~ 14oz) tuscan kale (aka black or lacinato) washed and patted dry
2 oz (~1/2c) pecornio cheese, grated or ground in a food processor
juice of half a lemon
freshly ground black pepper or red pepper flakes to taste

In a small saucepan over low heat, simmer vinegar, water, and raisins for 5 min, until plump and soft. Set aside in liquid. Toaste bread crumbs, garlic, and 2 tsp of oil ina skillet together with a pinch of salt until golden; set aside. Trim heavy stems off kale and remove ribs. Stack sections of leaves and roll them into a tube, then cut then into very thin ribbons crosswise (chiffonade). Put kale in a large bowl. Add cheese, walnuts, and raisins (leaving left over liquid in dish), remaining 2 tbsp olive oil, and lemon juice, and toss until all the kale is coated. Taste and adjust seasonings with salt, pepper, and some of the reserved liquid from raisins, if needed. Let sit for 10 min before serving. Just before serving, toss with breadcrumbs and, if needed, a final 1 tsp drizzle of oil.
